{
  "text": "The possibility of altered bile acid metabolism by the WKY microbiota is relevant for gastric emptying because increased levels of circulatory bile acids (usually induced by high-fat diets) upregulate nitric oxide synthase and bile acid receptor 1 (TGR5) expression in the gastric myenteric plexus, resulting in enhanced nonadrenergic noncholinergic relaxation and delayed gastric emptying in rats [CITATION_1] . We propose that the increased Lactobacillus in WKY microbiome can contribute to delayed gastric emptying and disregulation of lipid metabolism via bile salt signaling, although further studies are required to clarify this.",
